description:
You are a Database Administrator tasked with optimizing query performance for the database located at /home/ga/Documents/databases/chinook_perf.db. Using a connection named 'ChinookPerf', optimize the following four queries by creating indexes on the specified columns:

Query 1: SELECT BillingCountry, strftime('%Y-%m', InvoiceDate) AS Month, SUM(Total) FROM invoices WHERE InvoiceDate BETWEEN '2010-01-01' AND '2012-12-31' GROUP BY BillingCountry, Month;
Query 2: SELECT c.FirstName, c.LastName, COUNT(i.InvoiceId) FROM customers c JOIN invoices i ON c.CustomerId = i.CustomerId WHERE c.City = 'Berlin' GROUP BY c.CustomerId;
Query 3: SELECT t.Name, t.Composer, a.Title FROM tracks t JOIN albums a ON t.AlbumId = a.AlbumId WHERE t.Composer LIKE 'AC/DC%' GROUP BY t.TrackId;
Query 4: SELECT t.Name, t.Milliseconds/1000, g.Name FROM tracks t JOIN genres g ON t.GenreId = g.GenreId WHERE t.Milliseconds > 400000 ORDER BY t.Milliseconds DESC;

Create indexes for the invoices table (InvoiceDate), customers table (City), and tracks table (Composer and Milliseconds). Save the SQL used to create these indexes to /home/ga/Documents/scripts/create_indexes.sql. Additionally, document the optimizations in a CSV report at /home/ga/Documents/exports/optimization_report.csv containing the columns: QueryNumber, QueryDescription, IndexName, TableName, ColumnName, and Rationale.
